data.chText: （人生的）一段经历；（小说的）片段，插曲
data.enText: an event, a situation, or a period of time in sb's life, a novel, etc. that is important or interesting in some way

data.chText: 我倒想尽量把那段经历全部忘掉。
data.enText: I'd like to try and forget the whole episode.

data.chText: 书中最有趣的片段之一在第6章。
data.enText: One of the funniest episodes in the book occurs in Chapter 6.

data.chText: （电视连续剧或无线电广播剧的）一集
data.enText: one part of a story that is broadcast on television or radio in several parts

means: (电视连续剧或无线电广播剧的)一集

tr: film consisting of a succession of related shots that develop a given subject in a movie
a brief section of a literary or dramatic work that forms part of a connected series
a part of a broadcast serial
a happening that is distinctive in a series of related events

value.def: You can refer to an event or a short period of time as an episode if you want to suggest that it is important or unusual, or has some particular quality.

example.ex: This episode is bound to be a deep embarrassment for Washington...
example.tran: 这一事件肯定会让华盛顿非常难堪。

example.ex: Unfortunately it was a rather sordid episode of my life.
example.tran: 不幸的是，这是我人生中非常不光彩的一段经历。

value.def: An episode of something such as a series on radio or television or a story in a magazine is one of the separate parts in which it is broadcast or published.

example.ex: The final episode will be shown next Sunday.
example.tran: 下周日将播出最后一集。

value.tran: （广播剧或电视剧的）一集;（杂志连载故事的）一节

value.def: An episode of an illness is short period in which a person who suffers from it is affected by it particularly badly.

example.ex: ...people who'd suffered a third episode of depression in two years...
example.tran: 两年内忧郁症3次发作的人

example.ex: The new drug lessens the severity of pneumonia episodes.
example.tran: 新药减轻了肺炎发作时的痛苦。
